_001\", \"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_005\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_004\", \"mol_005\", \"mol_006\", \"mol_007\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P2\",\n      \"name\": \"Ornithine Route via Biochemical Cyclization\",\n      \"description\": \"Glutamate is converted biochemically to ornithine, which then cyclizes on montmorillonite clay to P5C and subsequently reduced to proline.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_002\", \"rxn_010\", \"rxn_005\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_005\", \"mol_012\", \"mol_007\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P3\",\n      \"name\": \"UV-Driven Butylamine Radical Route\",\n      \"description\": \"Surface chemistry: Butylamine, formed via hydrothermal or surface nitrile reduction, is frozen and irradiated with UV on TiO\u2082/ice yielding proline via radical cyclization.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_007\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_009\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P4\",\n      \"name\": \"Electric Discharge (Miller\u2013Urey) Pathway\",\n      \"description\": \"Primitive atmosphere (CO\u2082/H\u2082/NH\u2083/H\u2082O) subjected to electric discharge generates a suite of amino acids, including L-proline, via radical recombination.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_006\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": []\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P5\",\n      \"name\": \"HCN Oligomerization Aminonitrile Pathway\",\n      \"description\": \"HCN and NH\u2083 polymerize on molybdenite and montmorillonite, forming proline aminonitrile, which hydrolyzes to proline in surface pools.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_011\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P6\",\n      \"name\": \"Wet-Dry Prolinamide Condensation Route\",\n      \"description\": \"Surface and biochemical pools allow condensation of prolinamide to proline on montmorillonite clay with trimetaphosphate under wet-